Example Data QA Tests
import pandas as pd

data = {
    "age": [25, 30, None, 22],
    "salary": [50000, 60000, 70000, -1000]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)


def test_no_missing_age():
    assert df["age"].isnull().sum() == 0


def test_salary_positive():
    assert (df["salary"] > 0).all()
What these tests do

Test 1

Check if dataset has missing values

Test 2

Check if salary is positive

If data is wrong → test FAILS.

This is Data QA automation.

Automate Model QA

Now we test AI model predictions.

AI models can produce:

❌ impossible values
❌ negative prices
❌ unrealistic predictions

QA engineers write tests.

Example ML Model
def predict_price(area):
    return area * 300
Test Model Predictions

Create file:
Code
def predict_price(area):
    return area * 300


def test_prediction_positive():
    prediction = predict_price(100)
    assert prediction > 0


def test_prediction_range():
    prediction = predict_price(50)
    assert 10000 < prediction < 50000
What this tests

Test 1

Prediction should be positive

Test 2

Prediction should be in expected range

This is Model QA Automation.



